dct_title_s: [Geological Survey of England and Wales : one inch to the mile map. New Series.] Maidstone, solid and drift, sheet 288
dct_description_sm: Geological Survey of Great Britain. Great Britain. Geological Survey of England and Wales. Sheet 288 solid and drift. Great Britain. Ordnance Survey of England. North Decimal Degree 51.300000. South Decimal Degree 51.1333. East Decimal Degree 0.8167. West Decimal Degree 0.4000. In upper left margin: Ordnance Survey of Great Britain. Relief shown by contour interval and spot heights. Transverse Mercator projection. National grid system. "Original geological survey (solid) on the one-inch scale by F. Drew et al. published on Old Series Sheet 3, 1868 and 6, 1864. Drift deposits surveyed by C. le N. Foster, et al. and added to Sheet 3 in 1875 and Shet 6 in 1886. Re-surveyed on the six-inch scale in 1946-50 by F. H. Edmunds et al." In lower right margin: "Based on the sixth edition new popular one inch map parts of sheets 171 & 172, dated 1951.".
